21. Be5+{ Cutting off the rook's support to the  e4 -knight. }
21. Rxe5{ Forced. We give up the exchange for activity. }
22. dxe5
22. Qxc3{ Creating a passed c-pawn. }
23. Rxf7+{ This is an elegant way to keep the balance. }
23. Kxf7
24. Rf1+{ Getting out of the attack from  c3 -Queen. }
24. Kg8
25. Qxe4
25. Qd3{ White has enough activity to give perpetual checks, but nothing more. }
