12. Qd3{ This is another way to defend the  c3 -knight. We can continue our development. }
12. b6{ Preparing ... Bb7 . }
13. Rfe1{ This move brings the took to the open file and prepares  Ne5 . }
13. Bxc3{ The right moment to ruin white's pawn structure. We are ready to finish our development with ... Bb7 . }
14. bxc3{ White shouldn't trade more pieces with  Qxc3  when they are going to end up with a poor pawn structure. This makes it easier for us to target those weaknesses. }
14. Bb7{ With a very comfortable position. We can build up pressure against the  c3 -pawn with ... Rac8  next. }
