6. Qb3{ This move attacks the  b4  bishop and intensifies the pressure on the  d5  pawn. However, White brings the queen out a bit prematurely in the game. }( 6.Rc1 { is not a great move either. White aims to maintain the pawn structure intact after  Bxc3 , but we can confidently play }6...dxc4 { , followed by ... b5  or ... c5 , depending on White's response. This will give us an improved version of the lines we have already examined. } )
