7. Ba5{ We should avoid giving up our bishop if we cannot disrupt White's pawn structure. This variation is an improved version of the  e3 - Qb3  lines for White. They have prevented our option to play ... Qa5 .     Nonetheless, we remain in a comfortable position due to the tension in the center and the lead of our active pieces. }
8. cxd5( { White is seeking to exploit our vulnerable pawns. The sequence }8.e3 O-O 9.cxd5 exd5 { transposes to the position mentioned above after }10.Be2 c4 11.Qc2 h6 12.Bh4 g5 13.Bg3 Ne4 14.Nd2 Ndf6 { . } )
