7. a3{ Just like in the  Qc2   Ne4  line, white forces us to give up the bishop but we gain valuable time in the process. }
7. Bxc3+{ We happily oblige. }
8. bxc3{ And after spoiling white's pawn structure, we are ready to strike. }
8. c5{ With the typical threat of ... Qa5  & ... Ne4 . }
9. e3{ White needs to develop the pieces at some point. }
9. Qa5{ We develop a piece with a threat. }
10. Qb3{ The most active defence. White keeps the queen on an active square. }
10. Ne4( { Immediately attacking the weakness. }10...O-O 11.dxc5 { posed some problems. White has  Qb4  coming up next }11...Nxc5 12.Qb4 Qxb4 { . } )
11. dxc5{ The only way to justify white's play. White creates an isolated pawn on  d5  and hopes that the bishop pair compensates for the spoiled pawn structure and inactive pieces. Their threat is to play  Qb4  next. }
11. O-O{ We are finishing up our development. }
12. Qb4{ The most challenging. White forces us to retreat with our queen. }
12. Qd8( { Looking to recapture with the knight and opening up the bishop's diagonal. }12...Qxc5 { takes away the active  c5 -square from our knight. } )
13. Bd6{ The most ambitious. White doesn't want to give up the pawn so easily. }
13. Re8{ We can't give up our rook, of course. Our plan is to attack  d6  &  c5  with ... b6 / a5 . }
14. Be2{ Played with the intention of castling and keeping the bishop away from the striking distance of the knight after ... Nxc5 . }
14. a5
15. Qd4{ Keeping  c3  protected and attacking the  d5 -pawn. }
15. b6{ We continue with our plan of striking at the loose pieces. }
16. Qxd5{ The only way to justify  Qd4 . }
16. Ndxc5{ The brilliant point. We are ready to give up an exchange for activity. }
17. Qxa8
17. Qxd6{ Our activity fully compensate for the lost exchange. White's king is in centre, the  c3 -pawn is weak and the queen is stuck on the edge of the board. }
18. O-O{ white looks to finish their development. }
18. Rf8{ getting the rook on  e8  protected. We are ready to play  Bb7 / Ba6 . }
19. Rad1{ bringing the rook doesn't help }
19. Qf6{ With a very comfortable position. At the very minimum, we will recover the material with  Nxc3 - Ne2 - Ba6 . }
