10. c6{ We support our slightly vulnerable  d5 -pawn as well as we stop all  Qa4 + nonsense. }
11. Be2{ This is an inferior square. We are able to develop our worst placed piece, the  c8 -bishop. }
11. Bf5{ The rule of thumb in QGD structures is to exchange the light-squared bishops as black. White can try to be tricky still. }
12. Bd3{ With the intention of playing  f3 . }
12. f6{ Forcing the knight back to  f3 . }
13. Nf3
13. Bg6{ We are completely fine. We can play ... Qe7  next, reinforcing our support on  e4 , and preparing ... O-O-O  at the same time. }
