15. Nxc3
16. bxc3
16. Bxe5{ Otherwise, white would have played  c4 / e4 . }
17. dxe5
17. Qxe5{ It seems like we have won a free pawn but white can keep the balance. }
18. f4( { Opening more files. White relies on the fact that }18...gxf4 { is met by }19.exf4! { followed by  Rfe1+ , after which we can't castle anymore. } )
18. Qxe3+{ We can safely win the second pawn too. }
19. Kh1
19. O-O{ We are a couple of pawns up for now. White should play the next move now. }
20. Rae1{ Bringing the last piece into the game. }
20. Qc5{ Keeping the  e7 -square controlled. }
21. fxg5
21. Bd7{ White can win back the material after the bishop trade on  f5 , but after ... Rae8 , we are completely fine. }
