13. Nd7{ As usual, we are prepared to surrender the bishop pair for some valuable time. I'll reiterate: keep your pieces as active as possible in this variation. We are primarily concerned with activity and are ready to make some strategic concessions, like the bishop pair and pawn structure. }
14. Nxc5{ This is the only viable move for White. Allowing ... Rc8  with the bishop on  c5  would have been a disaster. The  c4 -knight would have been under tremendous pressure. With  Nxc5 , White at least has the bishop pair to compensate for the lack of activity.     However, it's important to note that White's last three moves have been  Nd2 - b3 - c5 , only to surrender the knight. We have developed both our queenside minor pieces during this time. Such an operation can only favor black. }
14. Nxc5{ Our minor pieces surely look intimidating! Our plan is to play ... Rc8  next, putting some incredible pressure on the  c4 -knight. White can keep the balance with  Ne3 , but this time even the computer agrees that this is easier to play for black. Just improve your pieces and create threats! }
