16. dxc5{ The tactical point white was relying on. White wants to recapture on  c4  next, keeping some space advantage and the pair of bishops. }( 16.Qxc4 { is a completely different story altogether. After }16...cxd4 17.Qxd4 Qxd4 18.Rxd4 { we have the important }18...Ng4 { with multiple threats of  ...e5 / g5 / Bc5 . We keep the initiative. } )
16. Qe8{ A very important subtlety. We keep our queen lined up for  e5 . }
17. Qxc4
17. Bxc5{ Threatening ... Bxf2  and ... e5  simultaneously. }
18. Qe2
18. e5{ With a slightly more comfortable position for us. Our bishop on  c5  is quite active, and there some glaring weaknesses in white's position, namely  b3 / a4 / d4 . We have gained back the space in the centre and are looking to play ... Qe6  next. White can't trade the bishops as they will be left with the bad bishop on  g2  for our good knight on  f6 . }
