17. Qxd8
17. Rfxd8{ We have to recapture with the  f8 -rook so that the  a8 -rook can come to  c8 . }
18. Nxb6{ Last trick. }
18. axb6{ The simplest. We keep the c-file closed and dominate the d-file. Our plan is to simply play  Rd5 - Rad8  and double up on the d-file next. Not a position where we can play for a win realistically, but there are always such options for white everywhere. Our job is to create an environment where white can go wrong. If they don't, we should be happy to split the point. After all, we are black.... }( 18...Bxb6 { runs into some practical problems after }19.a5 Bd4 20.Ra4 { the position is still equal, but white a tiny bit of pressure. } )
