9. Ba6{ Defending the  c4 -pawn. White should try to win the pawn back. }
10. Nbd2{ And okay, if white gets  Nxc4  in, white might have some hint of an advantage. However, we can disrupt white's activity. }
10. b3{ Forcing the queen to go back. }
11. Qc1( 11.Qc3 { would run into }11...Nd5 { , with a double attack on  c3  &  g5 . } )
11. Nc6{ Developing our last piece. }
12. Nxc4
12. Nb4{ We threaten ... Nc2 . Our secondary idea could be ... c5 - Rc8 . Black is on the better side of equality. }
