( { Chapter 14 deals with   }7.Ne5 { , one of the biggest challenges if you want to play for a win as black against the Catalan. Usually, white gets a comfortable two-result position where we need to suffer a bit. I think I came up with an extremely rare & an interesting idea that prolongs the fight and gives us the chances we want. } )1. d4
1. d5
2. c4
2. e6
3. Nf3{ White obviously develops a minor piece towards the centre. We don't need a very big explanation for this move. }
3. Nf6
4. g3
4. Be7( 5.Nc3 { is white's main alternative in this position. However, after }5...Nbd7 { we transpose to  chapter 10.  } )
5. Bg2
5. O-O
6. O-O
6. dxc4
7. Ne5{ The starting point of the chapter. White wants to recapture with the knight, and not let us  play ... b7 - b5 , unlike the  Qc2  variations. }( { The main line goes with }7....Nc6 { , after which white has couple of decent tries with }8.Nxc6 { & }8.Bxc6 { , where white keeps a comfortable position with chances to push. } )
7. Nc6{ This is the main line by far. }
8. Bxc6( 8.Nxc6 { also keeps some chances for white. } )
8. bxc6
9. Na3
9. Bxa3
10. bxa3{ White's pushing a bit due to space and better pawn structure. Our pawns are easier to attack than white's. }
