12. c4{ We're gaining space on the queenside and, importantly, preventing  dxc5 . We're still not threatening ... Qxa5 , but are prepared for ... Be6  next, after which ... Qa5  becomes a significant threat.     After  c4 , white's knight on  a5  lacks favorable squares. White has a couple of crucial attempts to consider. }( 12...Qxa5 { runs into }13.Bxd5 Ra7 14.Bxb8±  )
