14. Bxd6
14. Qxd6{ We have eliminated the important piece and all ready to complete development with  Be6 - Nd7  next, after which we'll be better due to the better pawn structure and the awkward knight on  a5 . }
15. a4{ The only way to stop us from reaching our target setups. White pokes our pawns. }
15. Be6{ Activity over Material. If our pieces are well placed, we'll retain enough compensation for the pawn. We are ready to finish development with  Nd7  next. }
16. axb5( { Setting up a neat trap of }16...axb5 17.Nb7 { , winning material. Unfortunately for white, we look to finish our development now. } )
