18. cxb3{ Pretty much forced. }
19. Nxb3
19. Qc4{ As usual, we position our pieces on the most active square. I believe this is an appropriate moment to conclude the analysis. Although White does possess an extra pawn, our activity amply compensates for the missing pawn. It's us applying pressure in this situation. The position has a high tendency towards a draw due to all pawns being on one flank. We'll introduce the  f8 -rook into the game next and perhaps improve the minor pieces. Of course, hoping for a win here isn't realistic. However, the level of play required to get to this point is quite extraordinary. Not even Magnus can perform at this level without prior preparation. Therefore, I don't think we should be overly concerned about this. }
