( { Chapter 18 addresses White's alternatives on move 4, excluding   }4.e3 { , which is covered in a subsequent chapter. The most critical among these is }4.Bg5 { , a move attempted by several top players. } )1. d4
1. d5
2. c4
2. e6
3. Nf3{ White obviously develops a minor piece towards the centre. We don't need a very big explanation for this move. }
3. Nf6
4. Qc2{ This has been tried by a few top GM's, namely Riazantsev and Artemiev. White's idea is to take back on  c4  with the queen, keeping space and preventing the  c5  break. Nevertheless, moving the queen so early in the game has its own drawbacks. }
