7. a3
7. Bxd2+{ Forced, as ... Be7  would run into  a4  ideas. }
8. Nxd2{ White is preparing  Qf3  next, so we play the natural move now. }
8. Bb7{ Developing our bishop and stopping  Qf3 . We would be better if we are able to consolidate our extra pawn with  a6  next. }
9. b3{ The point of white's play. }( 9...cxb3 { runs into }10.Bxb5+ { , followed by  Qxb3 , where white claims a small advantage due to the pair of bishops and better pawn structure. } )
9. c5{ Exploiting the fact that white's knight is on  d2 , and not on  f3 . We break open the position to eliminate space and exploit white's poor king positioning. }
10. dxc5{ Forced. }
10. Nbd7{ We bring our final minor piece into the game. }
11. bxc4{ Forced.  b4  was incorrect as our passed pawn on  c4  is more dangerous than white's passed pawn on  c5 , due to difference in piece activity and the unfortunate positioning of white's king. }
11. Nxc5{ We want to be the side making threats. ... bxc4  allowed white to improve the knight with  Nxc4 , threatening  Nd6 . }
12. cxb5{ White wins the pawn but it is not over. }
