10. h3{ The starting point of the chapter. White vacates the  h2 -square for the bishop, without giving up the  g4 -square. The drawback of this move is that we don't face any pressure on our kingside pawns. }
10. Nc6{ A bit rarer and stronger than the main move 10... Nxg3 . }{ At the time of writing, this variation was played only in a single game OTB and 2 online games. I played this against GM Adhiban online (and managed to beat him xD), and he tried the next day and won his game too. Shows the power of this line. With ... Nc6 , we keep the  b4 -bishop protected against future  Qa4 + checks, and keep the  e5 -square defended, which is necessary to play ... Qf6 . }
