13. Be6{ we defend the important  d5  pawn, so that we can play  Bd6  in some lines. }( 13...Bf5 { is the most active square for our Bishop, but after }14.a3 Nxc3 15.Nxc3± { our  b4 -bishop doesn't have a good square. We want to play  ...Bd6 , but that runs into  ...Nxd5 . } )
14. a3{ White can continue with their plan, but this time we have something up our sleeve. }
14. Nxc3
15. Nxc3
15. Bd6{ And we are able to part ways with our dark-squared bishop comfortably. White's weak king compensates for our poor pawn structure. }
