11. g4( { The most critical try, we start inducing weaknesses on the kingside. White has a few tries, but only one of them puts some pressure on us. We want to play }12.-- ...gxh3 13.gxh3 Bf5 { and }14.-- ...Qh4 { next, followed by  ...O-O-O . } )
12. Qb3{ The most natural move, in my opinion. White brings the queen out and increases pressure over  b4  &  d5 . }( 12.Rc1 gxh3 13.Bf4 { transposes. } )
