14. Nf4{ Puts pressure on  d5 . However, we ignore that and counterattack. }
14. Qh4{ Threatening ... Qxf2 . White is forced to play the next move. }
15. O-O-O{ Where white renews the threat of  Nxd5 . We cannot afford to lose the  d5 -pawn since our king is still in the centre. }
