17. Nxd5{ Forced, as white threatened  Nxc7 . }
18. Qxd5{ It seems white is much better due to the extra pawn, but we are not done yet. }
18. Qe7{ We're turning the tables here. We return the queen and aim to swing it to  a3 , where it threatens the important  c3 -pawn, as well as renews the threat of ... Nxf2 . White can maintain equilibrium with  Bb5 +, but if  Bb5  does not appear on the board, it's black who's in control. }
