9. h5{ We follow our typical plan of ... h5 - h4 , to meet  Be5  with ... f6 , and trap the dark-squared bishop. White has a few choices here. }
10. f3{ The main move. White forces our hand }
10. Nxg3{ We win the Bishop pair, but open the h-file for white's rook. }
11. hxg3{ Although we have the Bishop pair, we need to be aware of ideas like  g4 . Our  h5  is a bit weak, and so is the Bishop on  b4 . }
11. Nc6{ A very rare idea, and has not been tried in any of the top-level games. We remain consistent with our strategy of developing the knight to  c6 , followed by  ...Qf6 / Qd6 ,  ...Be6 - Bd7  and  ... O-O -O . }
12. g4{ Is the comp's top choice, but hasn't been tested yet. White's point is that after }
