9. Nf3{ The most-played move by far. White develops the kingside knight. }
9. O-O{ We finish kingside development too. White has several choices here. }
10. Bb5{ Doesn't help white and we can continue with our plan by playing }
10. Bxc3+{ Spoiling white's Queenside pawn structure. }
11. bxc3
11. Ne7{ Followed by the typical ... c6 / Nf5 - Nd6 . We have a weak square on  c4  too attack. Note that we want to exchange the light-squared Bishop with ... Bf5 / Bg4 . }
