11. Bd3{ Is a very tricky and ambitious response, tried by Gelfand and Firouzja. White brings the Bishop to the most active square without wasting time on  Rc1 . }
11. h6{ It's almost everytime useful to chip this in. }
12. Bf4{ The trickiest attempt, played by Gelfand. White prepares  Qd2 , creating a not-so-subtle threat of  Qxh6 . }
12. b5{ We ask white to bring it on! We look to complete our development. }
13. Qd2{ White is ready to sac on  h6  next, so this time we play our usual reply. }
13. Re8{ Preparing ... Bf8 . White can't sacrifice on  h6  anymore. }
