7. exd4
7. Nh5{ We have covered 8.Be3 in the previous chapter, and will be covering the other options here. }
8. Be5{ This is another popular move. White wants us to take on  e5 , so that  Nxe5  comes with a tempo, with the dual threat of attacking the  h5 -Knight, and  Bb5 +/ Qa4 . }
8. f6{ We attack the Bishop back with  f6  in the usual fashion. We are never afraid of playing  f6 , since it's an integral part of our plan of gaining space with  e5 . }
9. Bg3{ Forced. This is not an ideal square for the Bishop since we can always choose to chop it off with  Nxg3 . }
9. g6{ With the idea of developing the Bishop on  g7 , and not on  d6 . We can anytime trade the Bishop on  g3  with our knight, so we preserve the bishop pair. Our next moves are ... Bg7 , ... O-O  & ... e5 . Black won a beautiful game in  Gajewski,G (2626) -Alekseev,E  (2620) Moscow 2019. }
