{ In this chapter, we'll be dealing with the last set of  e3 -sidelines of the London system variations. There aren't many, and most of them transpose to the main lines, but it's good to be aware of move order subtleties. Please note that Jobava London & few other sidelines are covered separately in the next chapter. }1. d4
1. d5
2. Bf4
2. Nf6
3. e3
3. e6{ We start with  e6  to avoid all the  dxc5  lines. }
4. Nf3
4. c5{ White doesn't have many choices, apart from transposing to the main lines with  Nbd2  &  c3 . }
5. Nc3{ was tried by Magnus once. However, placing the knight in front of the  c2 -pawn is rarely a good strategy (Jobava London players, this is aimed at you xD). }
5. a6{ We stop  Nb5  and look to gain space with  b5  next. Black is on the slightly comfortable side of equality. }
