4. Nd2{ The key sideline of this chapter. White tries to delay  Nf3 . }( 4.Bd3 { starting with  Bd3  also doesn't have a great independent value. We can play the natural response. }( { ( }4.c3 c5 { will transpose to one of the previously checked lines after  Nd2 ,  Nf3  &  Bd3 ). } )4...c5 5.Nf3 ( { ( }5.c3 Nc6 6.Nd2 { transposes). } )5...Nc6 { we are threatening  ...c4-b5  next, so white needs to play the next move. }6.c3 { transposing to the previous  chapter.  } )
