8. f4{ The stonewall approach. White wants to play  Nf3  next, and cement the knight on  e5  at some point in the future. }
8. cxd4{ An important inclusion. White usually wants to take with the e-pawn. }
9. cxd4{ Creates weaknesses on the c-file, which can be exploited by us. }
9. Bd7{ We develop our final minor piece. }
10. a3
10. Ne7{ And look to attack the weaknesses on  e3  &  e4 . If white takes on  f5 , it opens up the e-file for our rook to attack the  e3 -pawn. We have a very comfortable game here. }
