6. b6{ We make the necessary move first, and keep the flexibility of playing ... Be7 - Bd6 . We are preparing ... Bb7  next. }
7. O-O{ White finishes the kingside development. }
7. Bb7{ We develop our Bishop. With  Bb7 , we have a greater control over the  e4  square, which prevents white's plan of playing  e4  & gaining space. }
8. Qe2{ Is the most played move. White prepares  e4  }
8. Ne4{ We prevent  e4 . This is why we put the knight on  d7 . Our Bishop on  b7  defends the  e4  knight. }
9. Ne5{ The top choice of engines. White looks to exploit our undeveloped king. }( 9.Nxe4 dxe4 { comes with a double attack. White can't exchange the knights, and  Bxe4  gives us the important light-squared bishop and the bishop pair. } )
9. Bd6{ We bring out our Bishop with a tempo. }
10. Nxd7
10. Qxd7{ We have managed to develop all of our pieces and control white from gaining space with  e4 . Our plan is to play 0-0 next. }
