10. exf6{ A non-standard, but a very strong move. The idea of  exf6  is to firstly stop all  Ne5  ideas. This gives us more chances to play  Qd6 - Rd8  and put more pressure on the  d5 -pawn. }
11. Be2{ White develops their minor piece and prepares 0-0. }
11. a5{ we want to provoke  a4 , so that  b4  square is weakened. }
12. a4
12. Qd6{ preparing  Rd8  }
13. O-O
13. Rd8{ White's pieces are terribly stuck. Even if we are not able to capture on  d5  directly, we can keep on improving our position. Our plan, apart from  Nxd5 , is  Qb4 , forcing the Queen back, and then developing the minor piece with  Bd7 . Our activity & pair of Bishops compensates for the doubled d-pawn }
