10. Bf5{ We are still following  our course.      Black plans to play ... Nd7  next. Let me just lay out the plans for both sides here. Black wants to finish development with ... O-O  & ... Nd7  next. Black will have to play ... c6  at some point. After that, we'll have two plans: either gaining space on the queenside with ... b5 - a5  or playing ... Nf6 - Ne4 . We have to be careful while playing on the queenside since it would create weaknesses on  c6 / c5 .     White wants to play on the queenside, hoping for a minority attack after ... c6 , with  b4 - b5 . Our knight is best placed on  d6 , from where it keeps an eye on  e4 , as well as the weak square on  c4 . }
11. Nf3{ The first point of deviation from the course. I chose to not include this in the course file since this move is not threatening at all. }
