3. Nf6
4. g3{ The Catalan Variation. White aims to position the bishop on  g2 , where it exerts substantial pressure on the  h1 - a8  diagonal. However, unlike the traditional QGD structures, the  c4 -pawn is significantly weaker, which we exploit in many variations. Just like in the QGD, we are somewhat space-challenged.     We welcome trading the light-squared bishops and seek to challenge white's center with ... dxc4 - c5  in many lines. We also often play ... dxc4 - b5  in various variations, to keep the extra pawn alive.     Our typical plan involves ... Be7 - O-O , followed by ... dxc4 - b5 , or ... c5 , challenging the center. In some lines, we advance the knight early on  d7 , to prepare ... dxc4 - Nb6 . White aims to maintain their space advantage and deter us from effectively challenging the center. The concrete variations are analyzed in the subsequent variations. }
*
